lhaji Hashimu-Shehu Gazura, a commissioner in the Zamfara Independent Electoral Commission, is dead.  He died in an accident on Friday.  The deceased was also a former member of Zamfara House of Assembly, who represented Gummi 2 Constituency.  His death was announced in a statement issued by Chairman, House of Assembly Service Commission, Alhaji Mansur Bungudu.  Bungudu said the deceased will be buried on Saturday according to Islamic rites.  “He died yesterday (Friday) as a result of a fatal motor accident on Yawuri Road in Kebbi State.  “The deceased funeral prayer is scheduled to hold at Gummi Emir’s Palace on Saturday,” the statement added.  